properties.Name: North East
properties.Description:
NAME: North East
Impact: Increased personal allowances will lift 34,000 people out of income tax and benefit over 940,000, Newcastle will become a “super-connected city”, receiving funding of up to £6 million, Local Enterprise Partnerships will get additional funding of over £10m from the Growing Places Fund

properties.Name: North West
properties.Description:
NAME: North West
Impact: Increased personal allowances will lift 95,000 people out of income tax and benefit over 2.5 million, the Government will support Network Rail to invest a further £130 million in the Northern Hub rail scheme, Local Enterprise Partnerships will get additional funding of over £31 million from the Growing Places Fund

properties.Name: London
properties.Description:
NAME: London
Impact: Increased personal allowances will lift 97,000 people out of income tax and benefit over 3 million, 100 per cent capital allowances for plant or machinery investment will be available in a designated area of the London Royal Docks Enterprise Zone, the Greater London Authority will get an allocation of £70 million from the Growing Places Fund

properties.Name: West Midlands
properties.Description:
NAME: West Midlands
Impact: Increased personal allowances will lift 74,000 people in the West Midlands out of income tax and benefit over 1.9m individuals, Birmingham will become a “super-connected city”, receiving funding of up to £10 million, Local Enterprise Partnerships will receive additional funding of over £74m from the Growing Places Fund

properties.Name: Yorkshire and The Humber
properties.Description:
NAME: Yorkshire and The Humber
Impact: Increased personal allowances will lift 74,000 people out of income tax and benefit over 1.8m individuals, the Government will support Network Rail to invest a further £130m in the Northern Hub rail scheme, serving stations in West Yorkshire, Local Enterprise Partnerships in Yorkshire and Humber will receive additional funding of over £71million from the Growing Places Fund

properties.Name: South West
properties.Description:
NAME: South West
Impact: Increased personal allowances will lift 73,000 people out of income tax and benefit over 2 million individuals, Local Enterprise Partnerships will get additional funding of over £23 million from the Growing Places Fund, the establishment of two Rural Growth Network pilots in the Heart of the Southwest Local Enterprise Partnership (which covers Devon and Somerset and the Swindon and Wiltshire LEP)
